{{Infobox football biography | name = Juan Peregrino Anselmo | image = | caption = | fullname = Juan Peregrino Anselmo | birth_date = {{birth date|df=yes|1902|04|30}} | birth_place = [[Montevideo]], [[Uruguay]] | death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|1975|10|27|1902|04|30}} | height = | position = [[Striker (football)|Striker]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1922-1935 | clubs1 = [[C.A. Peñarol|Peñarol]] | caps1 = 180 | goals1 = 102 | totalcaps = 180 | totalgoals = 102 | nationalyears1 = 1927-1934 | nationalteam1 = [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] | nationalcaps1 = 8 | nationalgoals1 = 3<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/uru-recintlp.html |title=Uruguay - Record International Players |publisher=Rsssf.com |date= |accessdate=2013-11-06}}</ref> | manageryears1 = 1962 | managerclubs1 = [[C.A. Peñarol|Peñarol]] | medaltemplates = | club-update = | nationalteam-update = }} {{MedalTop}} {{MedalCountry|{{URU}}}} {{MedalSport | Men's [[Football at the Summer Olympics|football]]}} {{MedalGold | [[1928 Summer Olympics|1928 Amsterdam]] | [[Football at the 1928 Summer Olympics|Team Competition]]}} {{MedalBottom}} '''Juan Peregrino Anselmo''' (30 April 1902 – 27 October 1975) was a [[Striker (association football)|striker]] for [[Uruguay]] who was a member of the champion squad at the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]], as he scored 3 goals in the tournament, including 2 in the semi-finals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-499059/The-forgotten-heroes-66-World-Cup-medals-last.html |title=The forgotten heroes of '66 get World Cup medals at last &#124; Mail Online |publisher=Dailymail.co.uk |date=2007-12-01 |accessdate=2013-11-06}}</ref> He was the first false 9 in a world cup. He also won the gold medal with Uruguay at the [[1928 Summer Olympics]]. He was a player<ref>{{cite web|url=http://carbonero.com/index.php/Idolos-1891-1929/juan-peregrin-anselmo.html |accessdate=March 14, 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/20091202104014/http://carbonero.com:80/index.php/Idolos-1891-1929/juan-peregrin-anselmo.html |archivedate=December 2, 2009 }}</ref> and later coach of [[C.A. Peñarol]]. As coach, succeeding mid-1962 the Hungarian [[Béla Guttmann]] in office, he led the club to the Uruguayan championship of the same year. In the later part of 1963 the Uruguayan goalkeeper [[Roque Maspoli]] succeeded him.
