{{MedalGold  | [[1920 Summer Olympics|1920 Antwerp]] |[[Football at the 1920 Summer Olympics|Team Competition]]}}
{{MedalBottom}}
'''Jean De Bie''' (9 May 1892 &ndash; 30 April 1961<ref>[http://www.olympic-medallists.com/BEL.html Belgium's first Olympic champions - olympic-medallists.com]</ref>) was a [[Belgium|Belgian]] [[football (soccer)]] player. He played as a [[Goalkeeper (football)|goalkeeper]].

During his career he played mostly for [[K.F.C. Rhodienne-Verrewinkel|Royal Racing Club de Bruxelles]]. He won the [[Football at the 1920 Summer Olympics|gold medal]] at the [[1920 Summer Olympics]] playing for [[Belgium national football team]] and, at 38 years of age, he was selected in the Belgian squad for the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]], although he never played a match at the tournament.

