'''Domingo Tejera''' (22 July 1899 in [[Montevideo]]- 30 June 1969) was a [[football (soccer)|football]] player from [[Uruguay]]. He was part of the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] team that won the gold medal at the [[1928 Summer Olympics]], and the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]] held in Uruguay.

Tejera played club football for [[Montevideo Wanderers]]. He made over 200 appearances and won the Uruguayan league twice with Montevideo Wanderers.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=MWFC.com.uy|author=Paredes, Dr. Manuel|title=Salón de la fama Nº 03: Domingo Tejera|url=http://www.mwfc.com.uy/data/contenido.php?idCont=447|language=Spanish|date=19 October 2009}}</ref>

Tejera made 20 appearances for the [[Uruguay national football team]] from 1922 to 1932.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[RSSSF]]|author=Passo Alpuin, Luis Fernando|title=Uruguay - Record International Players|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/uru-recintlp.html|date=25 April 2013}}</ref>

