{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2012}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Alex Thépot | image = | fullname = Alexis Thépot | birth_date = 30 July 1906 | birth_place = [[Brest, France|Brest]], [[France]] | death_date = 21 February 1989 (age 82) | death_place = [[Dunkerque]], [[France]] | height = {{convert|1.78|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}} | position = [[Goalkeeper (football)|Goalkeeper]] | youthyears1 = 1922–1927 | youthclubs1 = [[Stade Brest 29|Armoricaine Brest]] | years1 = 1927–1928 | years2 = 1928–1935 | years3 = 1935–1936 | clubs1 = FEC Levallois | clubs2 = [[Red Star FC]] | clubs3 = [[USL Dunkerque]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | nationalyears1 = 1927–1935 | nationalteam1 = [[France national football team|France]] | nationalcaps1 = 31 | nationalgoals1 = 0 }} '''Alexis 'Alex' Thépot''' (30 July 1906 – 21 February 1989{{cn|date=October 2015}}; born in [[Brest, France|Brest]], [[Finistère]]) was a [[France|French]] [[Football (soccer)|football]] player. He was the [[goalkeeper (football)|goalkeeper]] of the [[France national football team|French national team]] in the first two [[FIFA World Cup|World Cups]], [[1930 World Cup|1930]] and [[1934 World Cup|1934]], and an Olympian.
==Career== Thépot played for the [[football club|clubs]] [[Stade Brest 29|Armoricaine de Brest]] (1922-1927), ''FEC Levallois'' (1927-28), [[Red Star FC]] (1928-1935), and [[USL Dunkerque]] (1935-1936). After a good year with Levallois, he was selected to play his first international match against England in 1927.<ref>Source: {{cite web |url=http://www.allezredstar.com/archives/fr_alex.htm | author=AllezRedStar.com | publisher=AllezRedStar.com | title=Alex Thépot | accessdate=2007-01-03| archiveurl= http://web.archive.org/web/20061207154444/http://www.allezredstar.com/archives/fr_alex.htm| archivedate= 7 December 2006 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no|language=fr}}</ref>
From 1927 to 1935, Thépot played in 31 international matches, conceding 77 goals, and was captain of the French team 13 times.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fff.fr/servfff/historique/historique.php?cherche_joueur=thepot&submit=go | author=www.fff.fr | publisher=[[French Football Federation]] | title=Player profile and cap summary | accessdate=2007-01-03|language=fr}}</ref>
Thépot appeared in France's first ever World Cup match against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] in 1930, although he had to abandon the match during the first half due to an injury, being replaced in goal by [[midfielder|half]] [[Augustin Chantrel]]. Thépot would come back and play in the next two matches, but his team was unable to go past the group stage, losing to [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] 1-0 on a late goal, and 1-0 to [[Chile national football team|Chile]], despite having saved a [[penalty kick]] while the match was still 0-0.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tables/30full.html#gra | author=Naskrent, Gwidon S. | publisher=[[RSSSF]] | title=World Cup 1930 | accessdate=2007-01-03| archiveurl= http://web.archive.org/web/20070101051047/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/30full.html| archivedate= 1 January 2007 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no|display-authors=etal}}</ref>
==1928 Amsterdam Summer Olympic Games== He played France's only match at the [[Football at the 1928 Summer Olympics – Men's team squads#France|1928 Olympic Games]], a 3-4 loss to [[Italy national football team|Italy]].<ref>http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/</ref>
