'''Santos "Vasquito" Urdinarán''' (March 30, 1900 – July 14, 1979), known as ''el Vasquito'', was a [[football (soccer)|footballer]] from [[Uruguay]]. He played for [[Club Nacional de Football|Nacional]] from 1919 to 1933 (318 matches and 124 goals), playing the position of right winger. He was born and died in [[Montevideo]].

He also played 20 matches and scored 2 goals for the [[Uruguay national football team]]. With the national team, he won the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]] (without playing the final), two Olympic titles ([[1924 Summer Olympics|1924]] and [[1928 Summer Olympics|1928]]), and three Copa Americas (in 1923, 1924 and 1926).

