{{Spanish name 2|Vargas|Peña}} '''Luis Vargas Peña''' (1905 in [[Asunción]]–1994) was one of the greatest [[Paraguayan]] footballers ([[Midfielder#Winger|wingers]]) before the [[Second World War]].{{ref|1}} He was the first [[Paraguayan]] to score a goal for the [[Paraguay national football team]] in a [[FIFA World Cup]], accomplishing that in a match valid for the group stage of the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]] against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]], played on 10 July. Vargas Peña also had the honour of being the first captain for Paraguay in a World Cup.{{ref|3}}
During most of his career he played for the club [[Olimpia Asunción]].
