{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2012}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Adolfo Zumelzú | image = Zumelzu 1929.jpg | caption = Adolfo Zumelzú in 1929. | fullname = Adolfo Bernabé Zumelzú | height = | birth_date = 5 January 1902 | death_date = 29 March 1973 | birth_place = [[Buenos Aires, Argentina]] | currentclub = | clubnumber = | position = [[wing half|Half-back]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = | clubs1 = [[Club Atlético Tigre|Tigre]] | clubs2 = [[Sportivo Palermo]] | caps1 = ? | caps2 = ? | goals1 = ? | goals2 = ? | nationalyears1 = 1927-1930 | nationalteam1 = [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] | nationalcaps1 = 13 | nationalgoals1 = 3 | pcupdate = September 2007 }} {{MedalTop}} {{MedalCountry|{{fb|ARG|alt}}}} {{MedalSport | Men's [[Football at the Summer Olympics|football]]}} {{MedalSilver | [[1928 Summer Olympics|1928 Amsterdam]] | [[Football at the 1928 Summer Olympics|Team Competition]]}} {{MedalBottom}} '''Adolfo Bernabé Zumelzú''' (5 January 1902 – 29 March 1973) was a [[football (soccer)|football]] player from [[Argentina]] and Olympian.
==Career== Zumelzú represented the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] at the [[South American Championship 1927]]<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tables/27safull.html RSSSF South American Championships 1927]</ref> and the [[South American Championship 1929]]<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tables/29safull.html RSSSF South American Championship 1929]</ref> both won by Argentina.
Zumelzú also participated in the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]],<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tables/30full.html#argsquad RSSSF 1930 World Cup]</ref> where [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] finished second behind [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]]. He scored two goals in the tournament. He played club football for [[Club Atlético Tigre|Tigre]] and [[Club Atlético Palermo|Sportivo Palermo]].
== 1928 Amsterdam Summer Games == He played on the team sent to the [[Football at the 1928 Summer Olympics – Men's team squads#Argentina|1928 Amsterdam Summer Olympics]].<ref>http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/</ref> Argentina lost the final against Uruguay.{{CN|date=February 2015}}
