{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} '''Arnold Badjou''' ([[Laeken|Laken]], 26 June 1909 &ndash; 17 September 1994) was a [[Belgium|Belgian]] [[football (soccer)]] [[Goalkeeper (football)|goalkeeper]].
He played his entire career (1929–1938) at [[R. Daring Club Molenbeek|Daring]]. He was in the [[Belgium national football team]] squads in [[1930 FIFA World Cup|1930]], [[1934 FIFA World Cup|1934]] and [[1938 FIFA World Cup|1938]] [[FIFA World Cup]]s and played 3 matches in the 1930 and 1938 editions.
