{{Spanish name 2|Sota|García}}
'''Isidoro Sota García''' (4 February 1902 – 8 December 1976) was a [[Mexico|Mexican]] [[association football|footballer]] ([[goalkeeper (football)|goalkeeper]]) who participated in the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]]. He played in only one game (versus [[Chile national football team|Chile]]) and was beaten three times. Sota's club during the tournament was [[Club América]]. 
