{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2011}} {{Infobox football biography | name= Marcel Langiller | image = | fullname = | height = | birth_date = 2 June 1908 | birth_place = [[Charenton-le-Pont]], France | death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|1980|12|28|1908|6|2}} | death_place = | position = [[Striker (football)|Striker]] | youthyears1 = -1928 | youthclubs1 = [[CA Paris-Charenton|CA Paris]] | years1 = 1928–1933 | years2 = 1933–1934 | years3 = 1934–1936 | years4 = 1936–1938 | clubs1 = [[Excelsior Roubaix]] | clubs2 = [[Red Star Saint-Ouen|Red Star]] | clubs3 = [[AS Saint-Étienne|Saint-Étienne]] | clubs4 = [[CA Paris-Charenton|CA Paris]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | nationalyears1 = 1927–1937 | nationalteam1 = [[France national football team|France]] | nationalcaps1 = 30 | nationalgoals1 = 7 | manageryears1 = | managerclubs1 = }} '''Marcel Langiller''' (born in [[Charenton-le-Pont]], Val-de-Marne, 2 June 1908 – died 28 December 1980) was a French [[association football|footballer]] and is an Olympian. He played in a striker role, and was nicknamed "La Caille".
==Career== During his career, Langiller played before 1928 for [[CA Paris-Charenton|CA Paris]], [[Excelsior Athlétic Club de Roubaix]] (1928–1933), [[Red Star Football Club|Red Star]] (1934–1936), [[AS Saint-Étienne]] (1935–1937) and CA Paris (1936–1938). He won two [[Coupe de France]] in 1928 and 1933.
For the [[France national football team]] he received 30 international caps, with 7 goals scored, and participated in the first edition of [[1930 FIFA World Cup|FIFA World Cup in 1930]].
==1928 Amsterdam Summer Olympic Games== He played on the French team sent to the [[Football at the 1928 Summer Olympics – Men's team squads#France|1928 Amsterdam Summer Olympics]].<ref>http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/</ref>
