'''Juan Carlos Calvo''' (born in [[Montevideo]], June 26, 1906 – October 12, 1977) was an [[Uruguay]]an [[Association football|footballer]]. He was part of the team that won the first ever [[1930 FIFA World Cup|World Cup in 1930]] for [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]], but he did not play any matches in the tournament. He was a club player of [[Miramar Misiones]].
