'''Miguel Ángel Melogno''' (born March 22, 1905 – March 27, 1945) was an [[Uruguay]]an [[football (soccer)|footballer]] who was part of the team that won the first ever [[1930 FIFA World Cup|World Cup in 1930]] for [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]], but he did not play any matches in the tournament.  He also won the gold medal in [[football at the 1928 Summer Olympics]]. He was a club player of [[C.A. Bella Vista|Bella Vista Montevideo]].

