'''Conduelo Píriz''' (born in [[Montevideo]], June 17, 1905 — December 25, 1976) was an [[Uruguay]]an [[football (soccer)|footballer]] who was part of the team that won the first ever [[1930 FIFA World Cup|World Cup in 1930]] for [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]], but he did not play any matches in the tournament. He was a club player of [[Club Nacional de Football|Nacional Montevideo]].
