{{Infobox football biography | name = Zoilo Saldombide | image = | fullname = Zoilo Lucas Saldombide | birth_date = {{birth date|1905|3|18}} | birth_place = [[Montevideo]], [[Uruguay]] | death_date = {{death date and age|1981|12|4|1905|3|18}} | death_place = | height = | position = Striker | currentclub = | clubnumber = | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1923–1926 | years2 = 1927-1934 | years3 = | years4 = | clubs1 = [[Montevideo Wanderers FC|Montevideo Wanderers]] | clubs2 = [[Nacional Montevideo|Nacional]] | clubs3 = | clubs4 = | caps1 = | goals1 = | caps2 = 182 | goals2 = 45 | manageryears1 = | managerclubs1 = | nationalyears1 = 1922–1928 | nationalteam1 = [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] | nationalcaps1 = 15 | nationalgoals1 = 3 | pcupdate = | ntupdate = }}
'''Zoilo Lucas Saldombide''' [http://www.imcanelones.gub.uy/?q=node/4649] (March 18, 1905 - December 4, 1981) was a [[Uruguay]]an [[football (soccer)|footballer]]. He was part of the team that won the first ever [[1930 FIFA World Cup|World Cup in 1930]] for [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]], but he did not play any matches in the tournament. He was a club player of [[Montevideo Wanderers F.C.|Montevideo Wanderers]] and [[Nacional Montevideo|Nacional]].
