{{Infobox football biography | name = Juan Bottaso | image = Juan Botasso.jpg | image_size = 150 | fullname = Juan Bottaso | height = {{height|m=1.69|precision=0}} | birth_date = 23 October 1908 | birth_place = [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|1950|10|5|1908|10|23}} | death_place = [[Quilmes]], Argentina | position = [[Goalkeeper (football)|Goalkeeper]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1927-1930 | years2 = 1930-1938 | years3 = 1938-1946 | clubs1 = [[Argentino de Quilmes]] | clubs2 = [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing Club]] | clubs3 = [[Argentino de Quilmes]] | caps1 = 2 | caps2 = ? | caps3 = ? | goals1 = 0 | goals2 = ? | goals3 = 0 | nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] | nationalcaps1 = 9 | nationalgoals1 = 0 }} '''Juan Bottaso''' (23 October 1908 – 5 October 1950) was an [[Argentina|Argentine]] [[Association football|footballer]]. He played in goal for [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] in the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]] [[1930 FIFA World Cup#Final|final]] on 30 July 1930, which was lost 4–2 to [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]].<ref name="Argentina 1930 World Cup">{{cite web | title = Argentina squads in the 1930 World Cup | url = http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/arg-squad-wc.html#1930 | publisher = rsssf.com | accessdate = 2008-05-24}}</ref>
Bottaso started his career in 1927 with [[Argentino de Quilmes]]. After playing in the 1930 World Cup he moved to [[Racing Club de Avellaneda]] where he played until 1938. Botasso then returned to Argentino de Quilmes who were playing in the Argentine 2nd Division.
