{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2013}} {{Infobox football biography | name = José della Torre | image = Jose Della Torre 1936.JPG | image_size = 200px | caption = | fullname = José della Torre | height = {{height|m=1.79|precision=0}} | birth_date = 23 March 1906 | birth_place = [[San Isidro, Buenos Aires|San Isidro]], [[Argentina]] | death_date={{death date and age|1979|7|31|1906|3|23|df=yes}} | death_place = [[Lanús]], [[Argentina]] | position = [[Defender (association football)|Right back]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1925–1926 | years2 = 1927–1933 | years3 = 1934 | years4 = 1935–1936 | years5 = 1937 | clubs1 = [[San Isidro, Buenos Aires|San Isidro]] | clubs2 = [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing Club]] | clubs3 = [[America Football Club (RJ)|América Football Club]] | clubs4 = [[Ferro Carril Oeste]] | clubs5 = [[Club Atlético Atlanta|Atlanta]] | caps1 = | caps2 = | caps3 = | caps4 = 40 | caps5 = 2 | goals1 = | goals2 = | goals3 = | goals4 = 0 | goals5 = 0 | nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] | nationalcaps1 = 5 | nationalgoals1 = 0 }} '''José della Torre''' (born 23 March 1906 – 31 July 1979) was an [[Argentina|Argentine]] [[association football|footballer]]. He played in defence for [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] in the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]] [[1930 FIFA World Cup#Final|final]] on 30 July 1930, which was lost 4–2 to [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]].<ref name="World Cup 1930">{{cite web | title = World Cup 1930 | url = http://www.rsssf.com/tables/30full.html | publisher = rsssf.com | accessdate = 20 May 2008}}</ref>
After retiring as a player Della Torre went on to become a football manager, in 1958 he led [[Racing Club de Avellaneda]] to the [[Argentine Primera]] championship.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/players/arg-coach-champ.html rsssf: Argentine championship winning managers]</ref> He also managed [[Ferro Carril Oeste]] amongst others.
