{{Spanish name 2|Benítez|Arpolda}}
'''Pedro Manuel Benítez Arpolda''' (12 January 1901<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=198016/index.html |title=FIFA Player Statistics: Pedro Benítez |publisher=FIFA |accessdate=16 December 2010}}</ref> – 31 January 1974) was a [[Paraguay]]an football goalkeeper. In 1930, he played in the FIFA World Cup in [[Uruguay]], for the Paraguayan team. In 1932, he played 9 matches in the [[Club Atlético Atlanta]], in the [[Argentina|Argentinian]] First League. This club, in those years, was contracted a complete team of Paraguayan footballers.

