{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2012}} {{Spanish name 2|Subiabre|Astorga}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Guillermo Subiabre | image = Subiabre.JPG | image_size = 150 | fullname = Guillermo Subiabre Astorga | birth_date = {{Birth date|df=yes|1903|2|25}} | birth_place = [[Osorno, Chile|Osorno]], [[Chile]] | death_date = {{death year and age|1964|1903}} }} '''Guillermo Subiabre Astorga''' (born 25 February 1903 in [[Osorno, Chile]]; died in 1964) was a [[Chile]]an [[football (soccer)|footballer]]. During his career he played for [[Colo-Colo]] (1927–1934),<ref>{{cite web|author=Idolos: Delanteros |url=http://www.colocolo.cl/idolos/guillermo-subiabre/ |title=Idolos: Delanteros « Colo Colo - Sitio Oficial del Eterno Campeón |publisher=Colocolo.cl |date=}}</ref> [[Santiago Wanderers]], and the [[Chile national football team]]. He also participated in the [[1928 Summer Olympics]] and in the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=58531/index.html |title=FIFA Player Statistics: Guillermo SUBIABRE |publisher=FIFA.com |date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesc/chil-intres-det.html |title=Chile - International Results - Details |publisher=Rsssf.com |date=}}</ref>
At [[Colo-Colo]], Subiabre played as a striker for eight seasons, six of which were part of the amateur period and two of which were part of the professional period. In 1934, he was recognized as a lifetime honorary player for [[Colo-Colo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.colocolo.cl/2009/06/guillermo-subiabre/ |title=Guillermo Subiabre « Colo Colo - Sitio Oficial del Eterno Campeón |publisher=Colocolo.cl |date=}}</ref>
