'''Enrique Ballestrero''' (18 January 1905 –  11 October 1969) was a [[goalkeeper (football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] who was a member of the champion squad at the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]]. He played in all four matches of the tournament, including the final win against [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]].<ref>[http://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=46133/index.html FIFA chart] {{WebCite|url=http://www.webcitation.org/5vrHvTKZE|date =2011-01-19}}</ref> "Quique" Ballestrero played for the [[Rampla Juniors]].{{citation needed|date=November 2010}}

==Honours==
===International===
*[[FIFA World Cup]], [[1930 FIFA World Cup|1930]]
*[[FIFA World Cup awards#All-Star Team|1930 FIFA World Cup All-Star Team]]

