{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Alexis Chantraine | image = | caption = | fullname = Joseph Dieudonné Alexis Chantraine | birth_date = 16 March 1901 | birth_place = [[Bressoux]] ([[Belgium]]), {{flagicon|BEL}} | death_date = 24 April 1987 | height = | position = [[midfielder|outside-right]] | currentclub = | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1919-1937 | clubs1 = [[RFC de Liège|Royal FC Liegeois]] | caps1 = 368 | goals1 = 6 | totalcaps = | totalgoals = | nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = | medaltemplates = | manageryears1 = 1946-1947 | managerclubs1 = Royal FC Liegeois | club-update = | nationalteam-update = }}
'''Joseph Dieudonné Alexis Chantraine''' (born in [[Bressoux]], [[Belgium]], 16 March 1901 - died in [[Liège]], 24 April 1987) [[:fr:Alexis Chantraine]] was a [[Belgium|Belgian]] footballer.
An [[Defender (association football)|outside-right]] for [[RFC de Liège|Royal FC Liegeois]], he played 382 matches there,<ref>[http://www.rfcliege.be/historique/Pages/index/club100.htm on the site rfcliege.com]</ref> and he was selected for the first World Cup in 1930, but did not play.
