{{Infobox football biography | image = | name = Andrei Glanzmann | height = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1907|3|27}} | birth_place = [[Prešov|Eperjes]], [[Austria-Hungary]] | death_date = 23 June 1988 | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1929-1930 | years2 = 1930 | years3 = 1930-1935 | clubs1 = [[CA Oradea]] | clubs2 = [[Ripensia Timişoara]] | clubs3 = [[CA Oradea]] | caps1 = | caps2 = | caps3 = 36 | goals1 = | goals2 = | goals3 = 7 | nationalyears1 = 1930-1932 | nationalteam1 = [[Romania national football team|Romania]] | nationalcaps1 = 13 | nationalgoals1 = 2 | manageryears1 = 1946-1947 | managerclubs1 = [[CS Târgu Mureş]] }} '''Andrei Glanzmann''' (27 March 1907 - 23 June 1988) was a [[Romania national football team|Romanian international]] [[Association football|football]] [[Forward (association football)|forward]].
== Career == His career in club football was spent in [[CA Oradea]] between 1929–1930, is passed in [[Ripensia Timişoara]] in 1930 and he is returned in [[CA Oradea]] thin 1935 <ref>[http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/players/g/glanzmann_andrei.shtml Stats on Romaniasoccer.ro]</ref>
Glanzmann made thirteen appearances and scored two goals for the [[Romania national football team]].<ref>[http://www.frf.ro/echipa-nationala/player/381?page=1]</ref> He was selected in the squad for the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]] finals, but did not play.
