{{Infobox football biography | image =<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Petre Steinbach.jpg]] --> | name = Petre Steinbach | height = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1906|1|1}} | birth_place = [[Temesvár]], [[Austria-Hungary]] | death_date = {{Death year and age|1996|1906}} | death_place = [[Germany]] | position = [[Midfielder]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1925-1928 | years2 = 1928-1929 | years3 = 1929-1939 | years4 = 1939-1940 | clubs1 = [[CAM Timișoara]] | clubs2 = [[Colţea Braşov]] | clubs3 = [[Unirea Tricolor Bucureşti]] | clubs4 = [[Olympia Bucureşti]] | caps1 = - | caps2 = - | caps3 = 90 | caps4 = - | goals1 = - | goals2 = - | goals3 = 5 | goals4 = - | nationalyears1 = 1929-1931 | nationalteam1 = [[Romania national football team|Romania]] | nationalcaps1 = 18 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | manageryears1 = 1947-1948 | managerclubs1 = [[FC UTA Arad|UTA Arad]] | manageryears2 = 1948 | managerclubs2 = [[Romania national football team|Romania]] | manageryears3 = 1948-1952 | managerclubs3 = [[FC Rapid București|Rapid București]] }} '''Petre Steinbach''' (born in [[Timişoara]], [[Kingdom of Romania|Romania]], in January 1, 1906; death in [[Germany]], 1996)); was a [[Romania]]n [[Association football|football]] [[midfielder]].
== Career ==
During his career he has made eighteen appearances for the Romanian national team. His career in club football was spent in [[CAM Timișoara]] between 1925–1928, he has played in [[Colţea Braşov]] in 1928-1929 and he is passed in [[Unirea Tricolor Bucureşti]] thin 1939 and he has terminated his career in 1939-1940 with [[Olympia Bucureşti]]<ref>[http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/players/s/steinbach_petre.shtml Stats on Romaniasoccer.ro]</ref>
