{{Infobox football biography | name = Tranquilino Garcete | image = | caption = | fullname = | birth_date = 1907 | birth_place = [[Paraguay]] | death_date = | height = | position = [[Midfielder]] | years1 = | clubs1 = [[Club Libertad]]| caps1 = |goals1 = | years2 = | clubs2 = [[Atlanta]]| caps2 = |goals2 = | years3 = | clubs3 = Fusion [[Atlanta]]-[[Argentinos Juniors]]| caps3 = |goals3 = | nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]]| nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = }}
'''Tranquilino Garcete''' (1907–??) was a [[Paraguay]]an [[association football|football]] [[midfielder]] who played for [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]] in the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>[http://www.fifa.com/worldcup/archive/edition=1/teams/team=43928.html 1930 FIFA World Cup Uruguay]</ref> He also played for [[Club Libertad]]. In [[Argentina]], he was played in [[Atlanta]] (1932, 1933 and 1935), and the fusion [[Atlanta]]-[[Argentinos Juniors]] in 1934.
