{{Infobox football biography |name=Russinho |image= |fullname=Moacyr Siqueira de Queiroz |birth_date ={{birth date|1902|12|18|df=yes}} |birth_place= [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]] |death_date ={{death date and age|1992|4|18|1902|12|18|df=yes}} |height= |position=[[Midfielder]] |currentclub= |clubnumber= |youthyears1= |youthclubs1= | years1 = 1922-1923 | years2 = 1924-1934 | years3 =1935-1938 | clubs1 = [[Andarahy Athletico Club|Andarahy]] | clubs2 = [[C.R. Vasco da Gama|Vasco da Gama]] | clubs3 =[[Botafogo F.R.|Botafogo]] |caps1= | goals1 = | caps2 = | goals2 = | caps3 = | goals3 = |nationalyears1= |nationalteam1=[[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] |nationalcaps1= | nationalgoals1 = |manageryears1= |managerclubs1= }} '''Moacyr Siqueira de Queiroz''' (18 December 1902 &ndash; 14 August 1992)<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Net Vasco|title=Idolos: R - S|url=http://www.netvasco.com.br/mauroprais/vasco/idolos7.html|language=Portuguese|accessdate=2010-03-17}}</ref> was a [[Brazil]]ian [[Football (soccer)|football]] player. He has played for [[Brazil national football team]] at the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]] finals.<ref>{{FIFA player|63822}}</ref>
He played club football for [[Andarahy Athletico Club|Andarahy]], [[CR Vasco da Gama|Vasco da Gama]] and [[Botafogo de Futebol e Regatas|Botafogo]], winning the [[Campeonato Carioca]] in 1924, 1929 and 1934 with Vasco da Gama and in 1935 with Botafogo.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Folha Online|title=Especial - 2006 - Copa|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/especial/2006/copa/todos_os_brasileiros-1930.shtml|language=Portuguese|date=2005-12-09}}</ref>
