'''Jesús Bermúdez Tórrez [http://www.linguasport.com/futbol/internacional/mundial/Uruguay_30_squads.htm]''' (1902 in Oruro, Bolivia–1945) was a footballer ([[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]]) from [[Bolivia]] who played in [[FIFA World Cup 1930]]. He received eight goals in two games. He played for [[Oruro Royal]], whose [[Estadio Jesús Bermúdez]] stadium is named after him.

