{{Infobox football biography | name = Luis de Souza Ferreira | image = | fullname = Luis Alfonso de Souza Ferreira Huby | height = {{height|m=1.78|precision=0}}
| birth_date = {{birth date|1908|10|6}} | birth_place = [[Lima]], [[Peru]] | death_date = {{death date and age |2008|9|29|1908|10|6}} | death_place = [[La Punta District|La Punta]], [[Peru]] | currentclub = | clubnumber = | position = [[forward (football)|forward]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[Universitario de Deportes]] | years1 = 1926–1934 | clubs1 = [[Universitario de Deportes]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | nationalyears1 = 1929–1934 | nationalteam1 = [[Peru national football team|Peru]] |nationalcaps1= 2 | nationalgoals1 = 4 | pcupdate = }}
'''Luis Alfonso de Souza Ferreira Huby''' (born October 6, 1908 in [[Lima]] – died September 29, 2008 in [[La Punta District|La Punta]]) was a [[football (soccer)|football]] [[Striker (association football)|forward]] player from [[Peru]] who played for [[Universitario de Deportes]].
Souza studied engineering and made his professional debut with [[Universitario de Deportes]] in 1926. He remained with the club during his 8 years as a professional footballer.
==Clubs== * [[Image:Flag of Peru.svg|20px]] [[Universitario de Deportes]] (1926–1934)
==International goals== <small>Peru's goal tally first</small> {| class="wikitable sortable" style="font-size:100%" |+ ! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition |- |align=center| 1. || 14 July 1930 || [[Estadio Pocitos]], Montevideo, [[Uruguay]] || {{fb|ROU}} ||align=center| '''1'''–1 || align=center| 1–3 || [[1930 FIFA World Cup]] |- |}
==National team== He played for the Peruvian National Team from 1929 to 1934. In 1930 he represented his country in the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]] finals in Uruguay. In this competition he scored the first goal of one Peruvian team.<ref>{{FIFA player|58313}}</ref>
