{{Infobox football biography | image = | name = Diógenes Lara | height = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1903|04|06}} | birth_place = [[La Paz, Bolivia]] | death_date = {{death year and age|1971|1903}} | position = [[Midfielder]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = | clubs1 = | caps1 = | goals1 = | nationalyears1 = 1926-1930 | nationalteam1 = [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]] | nationalcaps1 = 9 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | pcupdate = | ntupdate = }} '''Diógenes Lara''' (6 April 1903 &ndash; 1971)<ref name="worldfootball.net">{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldfootball.net/spieler_profil/diogenes-lara/ |title=Diogenes Lara |accessdate=2012-02-18|work=worldfootball.net}}</ref> was a [[Bolivia]]n [[Association football|football]] [[midfielder]].
== Career == He made two appearances for the Bolivian national team at the [[1930 FIFA World Cup]]. From 1945 to 1946 he then managed the national team.
